cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.COMM, cs.DC, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the design of a wireless access infrastructure supporting multi-tenancy and mobility. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper may discuss security concerns related to multi-tenancy and backhaul. 
- cs.COMM (Communication and Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of Wi-Fi routers for small cell deployment and wireless access and backhaul. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) may be relevant as the paper draws inspiration from overlay techniques used in data-center networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) may be relevant as the paper may discuss information theory concepts related to wireless access and backhaul.
